# semantic-release autogenerated CHANGELOGs.
#
# `@semantic-release/changelog` writes CHANGELOG.md in a shape that
# does not pass `prettier --check`, then `@semantic-release/git`
# commits the file with `chore(release): X.Y.Z [skip ci]`. Because
# the commit carries `[skip ci]`, the CI format gate never runs on
# the autogenerated content — but the next non-skip-ci PR (any
# regular feature branch) inherits the drift and fails the gate
# through no fault of its own.
#
# Excluding the CHANGELOGs here keeps the format gate honest for
# code we control while letting the release bot own its own file
# format. Long-term fix is to add `@semantic-release/exec` with a
# `prepareCmd: prettier --write CHANGELOG.md` step to each
# `.releaserc.json`, but that's a separate per-package change with
# its own dependency footprint; this is the small unblocker.

packages/*/CHANGELOG.md
CHANGELOG.md
